-- Swedish FinMin says no bank tax in 2015
-- 
-- Mon Oct 13, 2014 04:33AM EDT
-- None



STOCKHOLM, Oct 13 (Reuters) - Sweden's minority coalition government will not introduce a planned bank tax in the budget for 2015, Finance Minister Magdalena Andersson said on Monday.

"It is not well-enough prepared to be introduced in 2015," Andersson told reporters.The Social Democrats, the largest party in the government, have said they want to raise an extra 4 billion Swedish crowns ($556 million) a year from banks.